		icon: {id: "pamhc2crops:cucumberitem", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Cucumber grows as a trailing vine crop producing fruit beside the main stem block, identical to melon growth mechanics; break the fruit block at maturity, leaving the stem to continue producing.", "Used in Pam's fresh salads, pickled vegetable recipes, and cold appetizers; cucumber's mild watery flesh pairs with onion and dill in cold-preparation dishes."]
