		description: ["Cantaloupe grows as a vine crop with a separate melon-block beside the stem — identical to vanilla melon growth mechanics; break the fruit block only, not the stem.", "Used in Pam's fruit salads, cold drinks, and summer desserts; the sweet orange flesh slots into melon-category recipes and pairs with citrus for smoothies and fresh bowls."]
